observation.description:
This Common Yarrow was seen at the Northeast Swale in Saskatoon SK. Although due to the drought, the inflorescence on this forb is very dry and colourless, the plant itself still shows major characteristics of Common Yarrow. This includes the flat-topped flower bunches, narrow pinnate leaves, and absent pappus. 

Keyed out through: Common Plants of the Western Rangelands - Volume 3 Forbs pg. 379 as Achillea millefolium (Common Yarrow).

EVSC380
